# Code Owners for Veld Framework

This file defines the ownership and review responsibilities for different parts of the Veld Framework codebase.

## Structure

Each section follows the pattern:
- Path pattern
- Owners (GitHub usernames)
- Review requirements

## Global Rules

# As a fallback for any unlisted files
* @yasmramos

## Core Framework Modules

# Core annotations and API definitions
/veld-annotations/ @yasmramos

# Runtime utilities, lifecycle, EventBus, and dependency graph
/veld-runtime/ @yasmramos

# Annotation processor (compile-time)
/veld-processor/ @yasmramos

# Bytecode weaver for synthetic setters
/veld-weaver/ @yasmramos

## Build and Integration

# Maven plugin for unified build process
/veld-maven-plugin/ @yasmramos

# Spring Boot starter integration
/veld-spring-boot-starter/ @yasmramos

## Feature Modules

# AOP support
/veld-aop/ @yasmramos

# Resilience patterns (Circuit Breaker, Retry, etc.)
/veld-resilience/ @yasmramos

# Caching annotations
/veld-cache/ @yasmramos

# Bean validation
/veld-validation/ @yasmramos

# Method-level security
/veld-security/ @yasmramos

# Metrics and instrumentation
/veld-metrics/ @yasmramos

# Transaction management
/veld-tx/ @yasmramos

## Examples and Testing

# Complete working examples
/veld-example/ @yasmramos

# Spring Boot integration examples
/veld-spring-boot-example/ @yasmramos

# JMH benchmarks
/veld-benchmark/ @yasmramos

# Testing utilities
/veld-test/ @yasmramos

## Documentation

# Module-specific documentation
/veld-*/README.md @yasmramos

# Main documentation files
/README.md @yasmramos
/CHANGELOG.md @yasmramos
/ROADMAP.md @yasmramos

## GitHub Configuration

# GitHub workflows and configuration
/.github/workflows/ @yasmramos
/.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/ @yasmramos
/.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE/ @yasmramos

## Build Configuration

# Maven configuration
/pom.xml @yasmramos
/veld-*/pom.xml @yasmramos

## Special Rules

# Any changes to build configuration or CI/CD require review
**/pom.xml @yasmramos
**/.github/workflows/*.yml @yasmramos

# Documentation-only changes can be reviewed by any maintainer
**/*.md @yasmramos

---

**Note**: As the project grows, we anticipate expanding the code ownership to additional maintainers.
If you are interested in becoming a code owner for a specific module, please reach out via
GitHub Discussions or email @yasmramos directly.

**Last Updated**: 2025-12-30
**Version**: 1.0.3
